To calculate the Current Assets Turnover Ratio, we use the formula:

Current Assets Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Current Assets

From the data:

Total Revenue = 851,679.79

Current Assets at beginning (Initial_date 2023-12-31) = 8,000,000.00  
Current Assets at end (End_date 2024-02-04) = 11,364,912.39

Calculate the average current assets:
(8,000,000.00 + 11,364,912.39) / 2 = 9,682,456.20

Then,

Current Assets Turnover Ratio = 851,679.79 / 9,682,456.20 â‰ˆ 0.0879

Rounded to two decimals: 0.09
